==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Yelper
<hw>Yelp"er</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>An animal that yelps,
or makes a yelping noise.</def> Specifically: <fld>(Zool.)</fld>
<sd>(a)</sd> <def>The avocet; -- so called from its sharp, shrill
cry.</def> <mark>[Prov. Eng.]</mark> <sd>(b)</sd> <def>The
tattler.</def> <mark>[Local, U. S.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Yelting</ent>⟦br⟧
